From: Shawn Guo <shawn.guo@freescale.com>
Date: Tue, 23 Jul 2013 22:49:04 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 0015/1074] ENGR00240987: ARM: imx: select SRAM for ARCH_MXC

Most of IMX SoCs have IRAM/SRAM integrated for audio/video uses, so
let's select SRAM to build in the generic on-chip SRAM driver support.

Signed-off-by: Shawn Guo <shawn.guo@freescale.com>
[Original patch taken from git://git.freescale.com/imx/linux-2.6-imx.git]
Signed-off-by: Biyao Zhai <biyao.zhai@windriver.com>
---
 arch/arm/mach-imx/Kconfig |    1 +
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm/mach-imx/Kconfig b/arch/arm/mach-imx/Kconfig
index 09708f5..51e37f7 100644
--- a/arch/arm/mach-imx/Kconfig
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-imx/Kconfig
@@ -7,6 +7,7 @@ config ARCH_MXC
 	select GENERIC_ALLOCATOR
 	select GENERIC_IRQ_CHIP
 	select PINCTRL
+	select SRAM
 	select SOC_BUS
 	help
 	  Support for Freescale MXC/iMX-based family of processors
